title: Represents a Update/Summary message. See Update/Message Summary Format

7DayYield.title: A price field, the value from a Money Market fund over the last seven days.

Ask.title: The lowest price a market maker or broker is willing to accept for a security.

AskChange.title: Change in Ask since last offer.

AskMarketCenter.title:
The Market Center that sent the ask information.
See Listed Market Codes for possible values.

AskSize.title: The share size available for the ask price in a given security.

AskTime.title: The time of the last ask.

AvailableRegions.title: String containing a list of all regional exchanges for which there is data available. See Listed Market Codes for possible values.

AverageMaturity.title: The average number of days until maturity of a Money Market Fund's assets.

Bid.title: The highest price a market maker or broker is willing to pay for a security.

BidChange.title: Change in Bid since last offer.

BidMarketCenter.title: The Market Center that sent the bid information. See Listed Market Codes for possible values.

BidSize.title: The share size available for the bid price in a given security.

BidTime.title: The time of the last bid.

Close.title: The closing price of the day. For commodities this will be the last TRADE of the session.

CloseRange1.title: For commodities only. Range value for closing trades that aren't reported individually.

CloseRange2.title: For commodities only. Range value for closing trades that aren't reported individually.

DaysToExpiration.title: Number of days to contract expiration.

Delay.title: The number of minutes a quote is delayed when not authorized for real-time data.

ExchangeID.title: This is the Exchange Group ID. Use the Listed Markets lookup to decode this value.

ExtendedTrade.title: Price of the most recent extended trade (last qualified trades + Form T trades).

ExtendedTradeMarketCenter.title: Market Center of the most recent extended trade (last qualified trades + Form T trades).

ExtendedTradeSize.title: Size of the most recent extended trade (last qualified trades + Form T trades).

ExtendedTradeTime.title: Time (including microseconds) of the most recent extended trade (last qualified trades + Form T trades).

FinancialStatusIndicator.title: Denotes if an issuer has failed to submit its regulatory filings on a timely basis, has failed to meet the exchange's continuing listing standards, and/or has filed for bankruptcy. See Financial Status Indicator Codes.

FractionDisplayCode.title: Display formatting code. See Price Format Codes.

Last.title: Last trade price from the regular trading session.

LastDate.title: Date of the last qualified trade.

LastMarketCenter.title: Market Center of most recent last qualified trade.

LastSize.title: Size of the most recent last qualified trade.

LastTime.title: Time (including microseconds) of most recent last qualified trade.

MarketCapitalization.title: Real-time calculated market cap (Last * Common Shares Outstanding).

MarketOpen.title: NOTE: This field is valid for Futures and Future Options only.

MessageContents.title:
NOTE: you can get multiple codes in a single message but you will only get one trade identifier per message.
NOTE: It is also possible to receive no codes in a message if the fields that updated were not trade or quote related.

MostRecentTrade.title: Price of the most recent trade (including all non-last-qualified trades).

MostRecentTradeConditions.title: Conditions that identify the type of trade that occurred.

MostRecentTradeDate.title: Date of the most recent trade.

MostRecentTradeDayCode.title: The day of the month corresponding to the trading day that a trade applies to.

MostRecentTradeMarketCenter.title: Market Center of the most recent trade (including all non-last-qualified trades).

MostRecentTradeSize.title: Size of the most recent trade (including all non-last-qualified trades).

MostRecentTradeTime.title: Time (including microseconds) of the most recent trade (including all non-last-qualified trades).

NetAssetValue.title:
Mutual Funds only. The market value of a mutual fund share equal to the net asset of a fund divided by the total number of shares outstanding.
NOTE: this field is the same as the Bid field for Mutual Funds.

NumberOfTradesToday.title: The number of trades for the current day.

Open.title: The opening price of the day. For commodities this will be the first TRADE of the session.

OpenInterest.title: IEOptions, Futures, FutureOptions, and SSFutures only.

OpenRange1.title: For commodities only. Range value for opening trades that aren't reported individually.

OpenRange2.title: For commodities only. Range value for opening trades that aren't reported individually.

PercentOffAverageVolume.title: Current Total Volume divided by Average Volume (from fundamental message).

PriceEarningsRatio.title: Real-time calculated PE (Today's Last / Earnings Per Share).

Range.title: Trading range for the current day (high - low).

SettlementDate.title: The date that the Settle is valid for.

Spread.title: The difference between Bid and Ask prices.

Symbol.title: The Symbol ID to match with watch request.

Tick.title: "173"=Up,"175"=Down, "183"=No Change. Only valid for Last qualified trades.

TotalVolume.title: Today's cumulative volume in number of shares.

Volatility.title: Real-time calculated volatility (Today's High - Today's Low) / Last.
